headline.main: ALLIES IN TUNISIA SPAR WITH ENEMY; Patrols Make Contact, While French Gain and Planes Pound Axis Bases ALLIES IN TUNISIA SPAR WITH ENEMY

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN NORTH AFRICA, Dec. 31 -- Allied patrols have been in contact with Axis forces in the vicinity of the station Bou Arada, twenty miles south of Medjez-el-Bab and fifteen miles west of Pont du Fahs, an Allied communique reported today.
abstract: Allied patrols make contact with Axis forces, Bou Arada area; French troops with Brit support take unidentified position, Heidous area; Allied planes pound Axis bases; Axis attack on Allied Tunis forces by Ger Lt Gen Nehring troops predicted; French Brig Gen Le Clerc's motorized forces from Lake Chad, French Equatorial Africa, continue advances in southern Fezzan; Rommel plight discussed
